Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_2848
Response Text: Consistent, on-going training prior to the applications coming out. Once they are dropped, the clock starts clicking and people have to find the opportunity, learn how to fill out their application, seek help and meet the deadline very quickly. I would like to see on-going training about how to apply, how to choose a venue, how to make your events more accessible, how to market your events, how to create a budget, etc year round—ideally taught by organizations or individuals who have received grants and are experienced with this. The City should apply funding towards this instead of teaching everything in house. This would make it more accessible to different demographics because there would be a lot of voices in the mix. This can also apply to how these opportunities are marketed.

